<?xml version="1.0"?>
<problem>
  
  <p>
A potential energy \(U(x)\) of a particle of mass m has a minimum at \(x_0\). The particle has a total mechanical energy close to the minimum potential energy \(U(x_0)\), and is undergoing small oscillations. 
<br/>
The angular frequency of the small oscillations is:
  </p>

<p>

<multiplechoiceresponse direction="vertical" randomize="no"><choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
<choice location="random" correct="false" name="1">\(\omega_0= \displaystyle\sqrt{\frac{U(x_0)}{m }}\)</choice>
<choice location="random" correct="false" name="2">\(\omega_0= \displaystyle\sqrt{\frac{1}{m}\frac{dU}{dx}(x_0)}\)</choice>
<choice location="random" correct="true" name="3">\(\omega_0= \displaystyle\sqrt{\frac{1}{m}\frac{d^2U}{dx^2}(x_0)}\)</choice>
<choice location="random" correct="false" name="4">\(\omega_0= \displaystyle\sqrt{\frac{x_0}{m }}\)</choice>
<choice location="random" correct="false" name="5">\(\omega_0= \displaystyle\sqrt{\frac{d^2U}{dx^2}(x_0)}\)</choice>

</choicegroup></multiplechoiceresponse>
    </p>

</problem>
